<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-09-16T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-09-16T12:00:00-05:00" n="372" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d372">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">835.01/16: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Bliss</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Buenos
                                        Aires</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-09-16T13:00:00-04:00">September 16, 1930—1
                                    p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 1:26 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>134. Germany and Paraguay have today recognized the new Government.
                            [Paraphrase.] I have just been informed by the British Ambassador that
                            he has received instructions to recognize on September 18. [End
                            paraphrase.]</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Bliss</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>